bxxW-4pJEuI.title: Quest for the Title 2 - Brian Chou vs Tremayne Dunbar - Kickboxing
bxxW-4pJEuI.description: http://www.mmaringreport.com/other-event-news/other-event-news/quest-for-the-title-2-results-2.html Local Brian Chou denied Tremayne Dunbar of Las Vegas the Mens ISKA Welterweight title with a unanimous judges decision. Chou was clearly the more well rounded of the two competitors mixing in kicks, knees and punches to keep Dunbars more singular boxing attack off balance. Chou used well-timed low kicks to batter the thighs of an opponent who appeared ill-prepared to deal with the leg assault. Dunbar dropped his hands far too low, far too many times - which gave Chou the opportunity to attack with punches and head kicks that landed early and often. In the end Chou pitched a shutout and took the decision with ease.

74jycyThvIg.title: Baltic Soul Weekender #5 Ann Sexton 'Rising Up' (16.04.2011)
74jycyThvIg.description:
Indoor Festival For Soulful & Electronic Music

WAS IST DER WEEKENDER? In England, wo sich an fast jedem Wochenende an Badeorten wie Southport oder Blackpool bis zu fünftausend Musikliebhaber aus aller Welt treffen, gehören Weekender seit den 70ern zum guten Ton. Im Alter irgendwo von Mitte 20 bis Anfang 50, feiern die Musikliebhaber allerdings nicht nur zu und mit Live-Performern, sondern auch zu den Sets der namhaften DJs, die zwei Tage und zwei Nächte ihre Interpretation von Soulful Music auf die Plattenteller bringen.

Der BALTIC SOUL WEEKENDER ist im Ostseebad Weissenhäuser Strand, einem international bekannten Erholungsbad im Norden der Republik, zu Hause. Ähnlich, wie beim britischen Vorbild, offeriert der Weissenhäuser Strand den perfekten Austragungsort und bietet mit Soul, Funk, Soulful House & seelenvollen elektronischen Klängen auf fünf separaten Indoor Dance Floors ein neuartiges Festivalkonzept mit einem einzigartigen Line-Up in einer unvergleichlichen Location.

Das Musikfestival für moderne Erwachsene: In der heutigen Musiklandschaft Deutschlands werden die modernen "über 30 Jährigen" so gut wie nicht beachtet, und ein Festival für gehobene Ansprüche gibt es nicht. Was aber, wenn man nicht mehr im Schlamm schlafen möchte, aber trotzdem gerne tanzen geht und gute Musik hört? Man fährt an die See!

vTpG48jOgWc.title: M1 Abrams versus Altay, Tank Key features
vTpG48jOgWc.description: M1 Abrams versus Altay, Tank Key features : The M1 Abrams is an American third-generation main battle tank produced by the United States. It is named after General Creighton Abrams, former Army Chief of Staff and Commander of U.S. military forces in the Vietnam War from 1968 to 1972. Highly mobile, designed for modern armored ground warfare,the M1 is well armed and heavily armored. Notable features include the use of a powerful gas turbine engine (multifuel capable, usually fueled with JP8 jet fuel), the adoption of sophisticated composite armor, and separate ammunition storage in a blow-out compartment for crew safety. Weighing nearly 68 short tons (almost 62 metric tons), it is one of the heaviest main battle tanks in service. Main Battle Tank Altay is an advanced third generation main battle tank, designed and developed by Otokar of Turkey for the Turkish Army and export markets. It is named in honor of Army General Fahrettin Altay (1880--1974)who commanded the 5th Cavalry Corps in the final stage of the Turkish War of Independence.

Cinq jeunes gens ayant grandi au cœur de la violence des rues de Compton, dans la banlieue sud de Los Angeles, durant les années 70 et 80, forment un groupe de rap, exprimant leur rage et leur vécu dans une musique brutalement honnête et accusatrice des abus des représentants de l'autorité, et donnent la parole à toute une génération jusqu'alors contrainte au silence.

ETFBn9RkLEs.title: League Of Legends - ALL IN - Katarina Vs Akali
ETFBn9RkLEs.description:
Patch: 4.16

From a dueling pov i'd say Akali has the upper hand until level 6. From a lane perspective Katarina has the upper hand. 

Myself i max q as katarina when i play against akali. Katarina's q does more dmg without the need to break the seal. Akali's is quite the opposite. And i just q to death akali until she is low enough that i can jump her.

After level 6 it will be tricky. If katarina waits to much for ulti she will get killed. If akali goes in without enemy minions at a safe distance to jump them if katarina ultis (or without flash) she will get killed.  

Akali's smoke screen won't save her from AOE dmg so even if she is invisible she still can get hurt.

LNW2Mr2fd1Q.description:
Skills, Goals & Assists from FC Bayern Munich's Thiago Alcântara

Born in Bari, Italy, Thiago joined Barça as a 14 year-old in 2005 and since then hasn't stopped growing as a player as he worked his way through the various youth teams.

Thiago has had a wide range of experience despite being so young. His father - Mazinho- was a professional footballer himself and so he lived in Brazil, Italy and Spain itself. When the family decided to move back to Galicia to live, Thiago began playing for Ureca de Vigo, where he soon caught the eye of a number of clubs, with Barça getting in first and signing him in 2005.

On 14 July 2013, Thiago signed a four-year deal with Bayern Munich, for a €25 million fee. The agreement also stipulates that a friendly will be played between both teams in the following four years, with Bayern paying €20 million directly, and the remainder being covered by Thiago himself and by friendlies previously agreed.

"Thiago is a special player. He wants a career in this world and we're fortunate that we've produced another player in-house."

J_w5q6RkQeY.title: [Hearthstone] Floating Watcher Choir. YYYES!!!
J_w5q6RkQeY.description:
Skip to 1:45 if you just want to see the choir!

One of the most beautiful sounds in Hearthstone sung by 5 handsome Floating Watchers.

For those who may be confused by the Mistress of Pain / Auchenai Soulpriest interaction: when the Mistress deals damage to any target it causes her to attempt to heal your hero. Since Auchenai changes all healing into damage, this results in the Mistress dealing damage to your hero instead- which then triggers her ability again, resulting an endless loop until your hero dies, or, for some reason, goes to -3 health. Who knows why that is :/

Because we bottom decked what we needed causing the original video to be 13 minutes long I've trimmed the video down to only the essential plays so you don't die from boredom. I'm just nice that way.
